en: Good map with cartoons, description of battalion operations

body.value: As the VII Corps was taking the key city of Cherbourg, the 297th stumbled upon the entrance to a large underground fortress. This ended up being a military storehouse for the German's Cherbourg garrison and formed the subcellars of Fort de Roule (Dubbed Fort Royale). Many of the chambers in the cellars housed thousands of cases of alcoholic beverages, including Hennessy, Martell Cognac, champagnes, wines, and calvados. The image depicts the gated entrance to "Fort Royale".
The "Jackrabbit" is the nickname for the 297th Engineer Combat Battalion
